==English==
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''microevolution'''
# small-scale changes in the history of [[life]], such as changes in [[allele]] frequencies in a [[population]] (over a few generations); also known as change at or below the [[species]] level.

===Usage note===
The term '''micro'''evolution was introduced to distinguish small-scale patterns of evolution from extinction and large-scale factors, which are termed '''macro'''evolution.

